-- DoCoMo, KDDI Disrupted in Northern Japan After Storm
-- B y   N a o k o   F u j i m u r a
-- 2012-04-04T01:50:15Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-04/docomo-kddi-disrupted-in-northern-japan-after-storm.html
NTT DoCoMo Inc. (9437) ,  KDDI Corp. (9433)  and
 Softbank Corp. (9984) ,  Japan ’s largest mobile phone operators, said
users in the country’s north are unable to make calls or send e-
mails after power blackouts following strong winds.  DoCoMo users are experiencing problems in parts of seven
prefectures, the Tokyo-based company said in a  statement  on its
website. Some of KDDI’s customers in Akita prefecture are
affected, while Softbank’s users are affected in Akita and
Niigata prefectures, the companies said in separate statements
today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Naoko Fujimura in Tokyo at 
 nfujimura@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
